@npbevo Hey there. 5G doesn't inherently use more data than 4G. It's essentially a more advanced version of the current mobile networks we use with technology that allows for faster speeds, lower latency and greater capacity. With this said, it's generally assumed that as we start to use 5G, we will naturally start to consume more data thanks to the attributes of 5G and how seamless it makes downloading large files, streaming content in Ultra HD and connecting multiple devices at once.
